name: Mount Flume

trails_config.name: Osseo Trail
trails_config.description: Ascends from Lincoln Woods using long wooden ladders on a narrow ridge. Provides unique southern views of the Franconia Range.
trails_config.parking_info: Lincoln Woods Trailhead, Kancamagus Hwy (NH-112), Lincoln, NH

trails_config.name: Flume Slide Trail
trails_config.description: A notorious 'Terrifying 25' trail involving steep, often wet, granite slabs. Must be climbed UP; descent via Osseo or Liberty is required for safety.
trails_config.parking_info: Liberty Spring Trailhead Parking, US-3, Lincoln, NH

current_conditions.ai_summary: Experience the beauty of New Hampshire on Mount Flume. At 4328 feet, this summit commands impressive views of the surrounding wilderness.
risk_factors: Check local trail conditions before departing.
Start early to avoid afternoon storms.

generated_description:
The Experience

Standing at 4328 feet, Mount Flume is a standout peak in New Hampshire. Known for its rugged and challenging terrain, it offers a quintessential hiking experience.

The Challenge

Hikers often choose the **Osseo Trail**, a **11.2 mile** route gaining significant elevation. As part of the **NH48 4000-Footers**, it draws peak-baggers from across the region.

Peak Bagging Logic

**Peak Bagging Opportunity:** Consider connecting this hike with **Mount Liberty**, which is just 0.9 miles away. Linking these peaks is a popular way to maximize your day on the trail.
